<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="231" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,151,1797]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,151,176]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named in honor of Professor Chandra A. Viraktamath, University of Agricultural Sciences, Bangalore, 
<collectingCountry box="[280,340,188,213]" name="India" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">India</collectingCountry>
, for his contributions to the systematics of leafhoppers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="231" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,151,1797]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,223,248]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Male</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[273,493,223,248]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">female and nymph</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[508,881,223,248]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Color and external morphology</emphasis>
. Crown with small, paired, dark brown markings, wedge-shaped or angulate, 1–2 small markings near ocellus, paired marking on disc (
<figureCitation box="[1144,1423,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,196,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[186,1401,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 17a–h. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus. a, b, c. Cradock, male, dorsally, female, dorsally and laterally, respectively; d, e, f. Waterpoort, male, female, nymph, respectively, dorsally; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626845/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Figs 17a, 17b, 17d, 17e</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with two paired round dark brown marking near lateroanterior margin. Tegmina with most cells with dark to light brown reticulations and large markings in costal, apical and claval cells. Hind wing with well developed jugal lobe and anal area. Nymph uniformly brown (
<figureCitation box="[850,943,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,196,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[186,1401,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 17a–h. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus. a, b, c. Cradock, male, dorsally, female, dorsally and laterally, respectively; d, e, f. Waterpoort, male, female, nymph, respectively, dorsally; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626845/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 17f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,151,1797]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,404,429]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[275,450,404,429]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Measurements</emphasis>
. Overall length 
<quantity box="[636,804,404,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.09" metricValueMax="5.23" metricValueMin="4.95" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="5.09" valueMax="5.23" valueMin="4.95">4.95–5.23 mm</quantity>
; crown length 
<quantity box="[973,1141,404,429]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.95" metricValueMax="5.1" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="0.495" valueMax="0.51" valueMin="0.48">0.48–0.51 mm</quantity>
; crown length next to eye 
<quantity box="[151,322,440,464]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="0.41" valueMax="0.43" valueMin="0.39">0.39–0.43 mm</quantity>
; pronotum length 
<quantity box="[543,715,439,464]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="0.58" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.56">0.56–0.60 mm</quantity>
; head width 1.5 7– 
<quantity box="[937,1045,439,464]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.64" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="1.64">1.64 mm</quantity>
; pronotum width 
<quantity box="[1260,1432,439,464]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.475" metricValueMax="1.52" metricValueMin="1.43" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="1.475" valueMax="1.52" valueMin="1.43">1.43–1.52 mm</quantity>
; ocellus diameter 42.6–58.5 µm; interocellar distance 48.7–57.9 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,151,1797]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,511,536]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[275,385,511,536]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Tergite X elongate, tubular, about as long as pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1180,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Figs 16a, 16b</figureCitation>
), ventrally with small, circular recess. Pygofer with wide anterior apodeme; pygofer lobe membranous, digitate, slightly curved dorsomedially (
<figureCitation box="[329,429,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 16b</figureCitation>
). Valve semicircular, with small anterior apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[1021,1120,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 16c</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate elongate, length to width ratio 1.36–1.75 (n=6), apex narrowly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[855,949,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 16c</figureCitation>
), medial margin divergent, about 5°, lateral margin uniformly curvate. Aedeagus with shaft elongate, straight, sclerotized in basal two-thirds, membranous apex (
<figureCitation box="[220,316,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 16e</figureCitation>
); dorsal apodeme complex, narrowly joined to shaft, positioned dorsad of shaft. Dorsal apodeme of aedeagus with posteriad paired tooth, curvate dorsoposteriad, anteriorly with elongate arms (
<figureCitation box="[1254,1423,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Figs 16d, 16e</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal paraphysis tubular, apex acute, extending beyond aedeagal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1104,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 16e</figureCitation>
), fused subbasally (
<figureCitation box="[1329,1423,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 16f</figureCitation>
). Style apophysis in dorsal view digitate, curvate (
<figureCitation box="[772,880,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 16h</figureCitation>
), in lateral view digitate (
<figureCitation box="[1222,1330,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1285,1330,799,824]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.6" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="g" value="16.0">16g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), angled dorsoposteriad; preapical lobe obtuse (
<figureCitation box="[602,703,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[658,703,836,861]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.6" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="g" value="16.0">16g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
); style situated near base of subgenital plate. Connective with transverse section convex and arms curvate (
<figureCitation box="[652,743,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,515,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,515,1847]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16a–l. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, dorsally, laterally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally, respectively; i. Connective; j, k. Valvifers 1, laterally, variation; l. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626843/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
Fig. 
